Introduce deploy parameters and initial .deb file support

In context of #1

An optional 'parameters' keyword argument has been added to deploy().
Pass a dictionary into it to attach parameters to deployed file.

Usage:
  p.deploy(stream, parameters={'a': 'b', 'c': ['d', 'e']})

Both strings and lists of strings are supported. Keys and values with
'=', ';' or ',' in their names are not yet supported.

Deploying .deb files can be done with with deploy_deb(), which is just
a thin wrapper around deploy() with parameters. Use it like this:

p.deploy_deb("./libatk1.0_i386.deb",
             distribution='ubuntu',
             component=['main', 'contrib'],
             architecture='i386')

You can specify lists and strings in distribution, component and
architecture.

Add support for sending client file checksums when deploying

By default when deploying files, client checksums will be sent.
This allows artifactory to check that file has not been damaged

Add possibility to get authentication information from global config

This commit adds a funciton read_global_config() that gets called
whenever the first ArtifactoryPath object is constructed. Then
it reads and parses configuration file ~/.artifactory_python.cfg,
which has the following structure:

[https://artifactory-instance.local/artifactory]
username = foo
password = @dmin
verify = false
cert = ~/path-to-cert

The configuration reading funcitons were generalized, since soon
a new class will be added, 'Artifactory' that will need those too.

    architecture the encode_matrix_parameters should be modified
    to handle URL layout specified in Artifactory documentation

    "For example, to upload package libatk1.0_i386.deb to both
     wheezy and trusty distributions, in both main and contrib
     components and both i386 and 64bit-arm architectures you
     would specify the following Target Path to upload using the UI:

     pool/libatk1.0_i386.deb;deb.distribution=wheezy;
       deb.distribution=trusty;deb.component=main;deb.component=contrib;
       deb.architecture=i386;deb.architecture=64bit-arm"

    http://www.jfrog.com/confluence/display/RTF/Debian+Repositories

Bump version to 0.1.14

Support for custom base URL

For uses who don't have /artifactory/ in base URL,
the library has failed to split the path properly,
because it uses /artifactory/ as heuristic for where
the 'root' ends and 'drive' begins.

As I didn't want to over-complicate the interface
of ArtifactoryPath (if it's even possible due to
pathlib constraints), I've implemented support for
custom roots via the configuration.

To tell the library your custom base URL, just put
that URL to ~/.artifactory_python.cfg like this:

[http://custom/base]

[https://another/custom/base]
verify = false

As you can see, other options can be specified as usual.
But then when you do ArtifactoryPath('custom/base/foo'),
it will be parsed as expected.
